column5: It was a very nice ride on July 29th, eastbound from Vermillion Bay. Far better than on the 22nd. -42
I made the return trip from Vermilion Bay to Dryden this morning.Much improved since last week,only one flag person stop & all the stretch had at least one layer of blacktop,no gravel or mud.
Should be done by Friday, all new road in the construction area's no more gravel
